1. Write down what these commands do:

make menuconfig

make -j$(nproc)

make modules_install

make install

update-grub

uname -r

2. After booting:

What does uname -r show before your new kernel?

What does it show after?

Did anything stop working (like WiFi, sound, etc.)? Make notes.

3. Open this file:

less /boot/grub/grub.cfg
Answer:

How many kernels are listed under menuentry?

Which is the default?

How can you manually choose which one to boot?

